1/*
2 Implementation header for FatFs Unicode support (header-only build)
3 This file is intended to be included by ff.h only. Do not include directly
4 from application code. It contains large static data tables for LFN/Unicode.
5*/
6/*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
7/* Unicode handling functions for FatFs R0.13+ */
8/*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
9/* This module will occupy a huge memory in the .const section when the /
10/ FatFs is configured for LFN with DBCS. If the system has any Unicode /
11/ utilitiy for the code conversion, this module should be modified to use /
12/ that function to avoid silly memory consumption. /
13/-------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

15223/*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
15224/* OEM <==> Unicode conversions for static code page configuration */
15225/* SBCS fixed code page */
15226/*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
15227
15228#if FF_CODE_PAGE != 0 && FF_CODE_PAGE < 900
15229WCHAR ff_uni2oem ( /* Returns OEM code character, zero on error */
15230 DWORD uni, /* UTF-16 encoded character to be converted */
15231 WORD cp /* Code page for the conversion */
15232)
15233{
15234 WCHAR c = 0;
15235 const WCHAR *p = CVTBL(uc, FF_CODE_PAGE);
15236
15237
15238 if (uni < 0x80) { /* ASCII? */
15239 c = (WCHAR)uni;
15240
15241 } else { /* Non-ASCII */
15242 if (uni < 0x10000 && cp == FF_CODE_PAGE) { /* Is it in BMP and valid code page? */
15243 for (c = 0; c < 0x80 && uni != p[c]; c++) ;
15244 c = (c + 0x80) & 0xFF;
15245 }
15246 }
15247
15248 return c;
15249}
15250
15251WCHAR ff_oem2uni ( /* Returns Unicode character in UTF-16, zero on error */
15252 WCHAR oem, /* OEM code to be converted */
15253 WORD cp /* Code page for the conversion */
15254)
15255{
15256 WCHAR c = 0;
15257 const WCHAR *p = CVTBL(uc, FF_CODE_PAGE);
15258
15259
15260 if (oem < 0x80) { /* ASCII? */
15261 c = oem;
15262
15263 } else { /* Extended char */
15264 if (cp == FF_CODE_PAGE) { /* Is it a valid code page? */
15265 if (oem < 0x100) c = p[oem - 0x80];
15266 }
15267 }
15268
15269 return c;
15270}

15272#endif

15276/*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
15277/* OEM <==> Unicode conversions for static code page configuration */
15278/* DBCS fixed code page */
15279/*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
15280
15281#if FF_CODE_PAGE >= 900
15282WCHAR ff_uni2oem ( /* Returns OEM code character, zero on error */
15283 DWORD uni, /* UTF-16 encoded character to be converted */
15284 WORD cp /* Code page for the conversion */
15285)
15286{
15287 const WCHAR *p;
15288 WCHAR c = 0, uc;
15289 UINT i = 0, n, li, hi;
15290
15291
15292 if (uni < 0x80) { /* ASCII? */
15293 c = (WCHAR)uni;
15294
15295 } else { /* Non-ASCII */
15296 if (uni < 0x10000 && cp == FF_CODE_PAGE) { /* Is it in BMP and valid code page? */
15297 uc = (WCHAR)uni;
15298 p = CVTBL(uni2oem, FF_CODE_PAGE);
15299 hi = sizeof CVTBL(uni2oem, FF_CODE_PAGE) / 4 - 1;
15300 li = 0;
15301 for (n = 16; n; n--) {
15302 i = li + (hi - li) / 2;
15303 if (uc == p[i * 2]) break;
15304 if (uc > p[i * 2]) {
15305 li = i;
15306 } else {
15307 hi = i;
15308 }
15309 }
15310 if (n != 0) c = p[i * 2 + 1];
15311 }
15312 }
15313
15314 return c;
15315}

15318WCHAR ff_oem2uni ( /* Returns Unicode character in UTF-16, zero on error */
15319 WCHAR oem, /* OEM code to be converted */
15320 WORD cp /* Code page for the conversion */
15321)
15322{
15323 const WCHAR *p;
15324 WCHAR c = 0;
15325 UINT i = 0, n, li, hi;
15326
15327
15328 if (oem < 0x80) { /* ASCII? */
15329 c = oem;
15330
15331 } else { /* Extended char */
15332 if (cp == FF_CODE_PAGE) { /* Is it valid code page? */
15333 p = CVTBL(oem2uni, FF_CODE_PAGE);
15334 hi = sizeof CVTBL(oem2uni, FF_CODE_PAGE) / 4 - 1;
15335 li = 0;
15336 for (n = 16; n; n--) {
15337 i = li + (hi - li) / 2;
15338 if (oem == p[i * 2]) break;
15339 if (oem > p[i * 2]) {
15340 li = i;
15341 } else {
15342 hi = i;
15343 }
15344 }
15345 if (n != 0) c = p[i * 2 + 1];
15346 }
15347 }
15348
15349 return c;
15350}

15355/*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
15356/* OEM <==> Unicode conversions for dynamic code page configuration */
15357/*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
15358
15359#if FF_CODE_PAGE == 0
15360
15361static const WORD cp_code[] = { 437, 720, 737, 771, 775, 850, 852, 855, 857, 860, 861, 862, 863, 864, 865, 866, 869, 0};
15362static const WCHAR* const cp_table[] = {uc437, uc720, uc737, uc771, uc775, uc850, uc852, uc855, uc857, uc860, uc861, uc862, uc863, uc864, uc865, uc866, uc869, 0};
15363
15364
15365WCHAR ff_uni2oem ( /* Returns OEM code character, zero on error */
15366 DWORD uni, /* UTF-16 encoded character to be converted */
15367 WORD cp /* Code page for the conversion */
15368)
15369{
15370 const WCHAR *p;
15371 WCHAR c = 0, uc;
15372 UINT i, n, li, hi;
15373
15374
15375 if (uni < 0x80) { /* ASCII? */
15376 c = (WCHAR)uni;
15377
15378 } else { /* Non-ASCII */
15379 if (uni < 0x10000) { /* Is it in BMP? */
15380 uc = (WCHAR)uni;
15381 p = 0;
15382 if (cp < 900) { /* SBCS */
15383 for (i = 0; cp_code[i] != 0 && cp_code[i] != cp; i++) ; /* Get conversion table */
15384 p = cp_table[i];
15385 if (p) { /* Is it valid code page ? */
15386 for (c = 0; c < 0x80 && uc != p[c]; c++) ; /* Find OEM code in the table */
15387 c = (c + 0x80) & 0xFF;
15388 }
15389 } else { /* DBCS */
15390 switch (cp) { /* Get conversion table */
15391 case 932 : p = uni2oem932; hi = sizeof uni2oem932 / 4 - 1; break;
15392 case 936 : p = uni2oem936; hi = sizeof uni2oem936 / 4 - 1; break;
15393 case 949 : p = uni2oem949; hi = sizeof uni2oem949 / 4 - 1; break;
15394 case 950 : p = uni2oem950; hi = sizeof uni2oem950 / 4 - 1; break;
15395 }
15396 if (p) { /* Is it valid code page? */
15397 li = 0;
15398 for (n = 16; n; n--) { /* Find OEM code */
15399 i = li + (hi - li) / 2;
15400 if (uc == p[i * 2]) break;
15401 if (uc > p[i * 2]) {
15402 li = i;
15403 } else {
15404 hi = i;
15405 }
15406 }
15407 if (n != 0) c = p[i * 2 + 1];
15408 }
15409 }

15417WCHAR ff_oem2uni ( /* Returns Unicode character in UTF-16, zero on error */
15418 WCHAR oem, /* OEM code to be converted (DBC if >=0x100) */
15419 WORD cp /* Code page for the conversion */
15420)
15421{
15422 const WCHAR *p;
15423 WCHAR c = 0;
15424 UINT i, n, li, hi;
15425
15426
15427 if (oem < 0x80) { /* ASCII? */
15428 c = oem;
15429
15430 } else { /* Extended char */
15431 p = 0;
15432 if (cp < 900) { /* SBCS */
15433 for (i = 0; cp_code[i] != 0 && cp_code[i] != cp; i++) ; /* Get table */
15434 p = cp_table[i];
15435 if (p) { /* Is it a valid CP ? */
15436 if (oem < 0x100) c = p[oem - 0x80];
15437 }
15438 } else { /* DBCS */
15439 switch (cp) {
15440 case 932 : p = oem2uni932; hi = sizeof oem2uni932 / 4 - 1; break;
15441 case 936 : p = oem2uni936; hi = sizeof oem2uni936 / 4 - 1; break;
15442 case 949 : p = oem2uni949; hi = sizeof oem2uni949 / 4 - 1; break;
15443 case 950 : p = oem2uni950; hi = sizeof oem2uni950 / 4 - 1; break;
15444 }
15445 if (p) {
15446 li = 0;
15447 for (n = 16; n; n--) {
15448 i = li + (hi - li) / 2;
15449 if (oem == p[i * 2]) break;
15450 if (oem > p[i * 2]) {
15451 li = i;
15452 } else {
15453 hi = i;
15454 }
15455 }
15456 if (n != 0) c = p[i * 2 + 1];
15457 }
15458 }
15459 }
15460
15461 return c;
15462}
